column1: Table Title: Changes In Total Demand In Chained (2015) Dollars, Quarterly

For more information on national accounts methodologies, please visit Singstat website (www.singstat.gov.sg/find-data/search-by-theme/economy/national-accounts/publications-and-methodology) to view and download related publications.
Total Demand -> Total Domestic Demand -> Changes In Inventories (Per Cent):
For inventories, this refers instead to change as a percentage of GDP in the previous year.
The sum of changes in inventories and exports of goods and services.
The sum of private consumption expenditure of households including non-profit institutions serving households, government consumption expenditure and gross fixed capital formation.
Acquisitions, less disposals, of fixed assets during the accounting period plus improvements to land.
The amount of materials and supplies, work-in-progress, finished goods and goods for resale.
The sum of total domestic demand and external demand. Contribution to total demand of a segment is derived by taking total demand as the base.
The sum of private consumption expenditure of households including non-profit institutions serving households, government consumption expenditure and gross capital formation.
na   not available or not applicable
-     nil or negligible or not significant
Numbers may not add up to the totals due to rounding.
Data are the latest available at the time of access or download. Some statistics, particularly those for the most recent time periods, are provisional and may be subject to revision at a later date.
Values are shown in Singapore dollars (unless otherwise specified).
